Array

Array DS:- Built-in DS. Stores similar types of data in sequential memory location
Array memory allocation:- sequential memory allotted by compiler & elements stored row by row in RAM

Array implementation:-
    1. using array module:- standard library comes with python
    2. using numpy module:- third party module, need to install using pip

Array operations:-
	1. creating empty array
	2. creating array with elements
	3. inserting an element
	4. traversing an array
	5. accessing an element with index
	6. searching an element
	7. deleting an element

More operations:-
	8. append element at the end
	9. extend array by adding another array
	10. add list using fromlist()
	11. remove last element using pop()
	12. finding element using index()
	13. reversing an array using reverse()
	14. array buffer memory start info & no. of elements in an array using buffer_info()
	15. counting occurance of specific element using count()
	16. converting integers to strings & vice-versa using tobytes() & frombytes()

#tobytes()
from array import *

arr1 = array('i', [1, 2, 3, 4, 1, 1])
bt = arr1.tobytes()
print(bt)

#frombytes()
ints = array('i')
ints.frombytes(bt)
print(ints)

    17. converting array into list using tolist() - print(arr1.tolist())
    18. slicing elements using [:]